%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FInsider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESam%20Bankman-Fried%20took%20the%20stand%20in%20his%20trial%20in%20a%20rare%20hearing%20without%20the%20jury's%20presence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDuring%20questioning%2C%20he%20often%20meandered%2C%20dodged%2C%20and%20rephrased%20questions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20judge%20will%20take%20the%20night%20to%20decide%20whether%20the%20jury%20can%20hear%20Bankman-Fried's%20testimony.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20unusual%2C%20tense%20hearing%20Thursday%20afternoon%2C%20the%20judge%20in%20Sam%20Bankman-Fried's%20criminal%20fraud%20trial%20criticized%20his%20%26quot%3Binteresting%2C%26quot%3B%20often%20circuitous%20answers%20to%20questions%20about%20whether%20he%20used%20funds%20belonging%20to%20customers%20of%20his%20cryptocurrency%20exchange%20for%20his%20own%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankman-Fried%20took%20the%20witness%20stand%20in%20a%20downtown%20Manhattan%20courtroom%20after%20jurors%20were%20sent%20home%20for%20the%20afternoon.%20US%20District%20Judge%20Lewis%20Kaplan%20offered%20him%20the%20opportunity%20to%20testify%20about%20his%20conversations%20with%20lawyers%20during%20his%20time%20at%20FTX%2C%20which%20Bankman-Fried's%20current%20legal%20team%20argues%20is%20evidence%20that%20he%20acted%20by-the-book%20and%20in%20good%20faith%20when%20the%20cryptocurrency%20exchange%20collapsed%20in%20late%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaplan%20has%20indicated%20in%20previous%20rulings%20that%20those%20discussions%20have%20little%20to%20do%20with%20the%20charges%20at%20hand%20%E2%80%94%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-sbf-fraud-trial-ftx-explainer-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBankman-Fried%20allegedly%20defrauded%20customers%20and%20investors%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20laundered%20the%20money%20for%20his%20own%20benefit%20%E2%80%94%20and%20should%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20be%20presented%20to%20the%20jury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20Thursday's%20hearing%2C%20Kaplan%20seemed%20more%20skeptical%20than%20ever%20of%20the%20arguments.%20He%20suggested%20the%20situation%20was%20comparable%20to%20someone%20who%20bought%20a%20house%20with%20funds%20he%20robbed%20from%20a%20bank%2C%20but%20didn't%20tell%20his%20real%20estate%20lawyer%20where%20the%20money%20came%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20witness%20has%20what%20I'll%20simply%20call%20an%20interesting%20way%20of%20responding%20to%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20Kaplan%20said%20during%20the%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20highly-anticipated%20testimony%2C%20Bankman-Fried%20hedged%20in%20his%20answers%2C%20sometimes%20taking%20a%20long%20pause%20or%20asking%20for%20a%20moment%20to%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20some%20of%20the%20issues%20that%20prosecutors%20had%20indicated%20were%20elements%20of%20fraud%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20keeping%20all%20FTX%20customer%20funds%20in%20one%20big%20bank%20account%2C%20allowing%20his%20cryptocurrency%20hedge%20fund%20Alameda%20Research%20to%20have%20a%20negative%20balance%20on%20the%20exchange%2C%20taking%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20personal%20loans%20from%20the%20company%2C%20and%20auto-deleting%20messages%20%E2%80%94%20were%20either%20normal%20industry%20practices%20or%20formalized%20with%20his%20legal%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Bankman-Fried%20consulted%20with%20counsel%20and%20took%20comfort%20in%20their%20counsel%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20criminal%20defense%20lawyer%20Mark%20Cohen%20told%20Kaplan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESBF%20gave%20rambling%20answers%20during%20cross-examination%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20cross-examination%2C%20Bankman-Fried%20hunched%20forward%20and%20kept%20his%20hands%20in%20his%20lap.%20He%20tilted%20his%20torso%20side-to-side%2C%20like%20a%20boxer%20dodging%20punches%2C%20and%20answered%20many%20questions%20from%20Assistant%20US%20Attorney%20Danielle%20Sassoon%20with%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20specifically%20recall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20often%20rephrased%20questions%20before%20answering%20them%2C%20sometimes%20telling%20Sassoon%20that%20he%20would%20answer%20the%20%26quot%3Bquestion%20I%20understand%20you%20to%20be%20trying%20to%20ask.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaplan%20had%20to%20remind%20Bankman-Fried%20to%20%26quot%3Blisten%20to%20the%20question%20and%20answer%20the%20question%20directly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20apologize%2C%26quot%3B%20Bankman-Fried%20said%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%2011%20different%20apologies%20he%20gave%20on%20the%20witness%20stand%20about%20his%20meandering%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Sassoon%20asked%20Bankman-Fried%20directly%20if%20he%20discussed%20spending%20FTX%20customer%20deposits%20with%20his%20lawyers%2C%20he%20took%20a%20long%20pause%20and%20looked%20down%20before%20he%20answered%20the%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20recall%20any%20conversations%20that%20were%20contemporaneous%20and%20phrased%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20certainly%20in%20retrospect%20wish%20that%20I%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22SBF%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653aabe8356802a56be50ba9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaroline%20Ellison%2C%20Gary%20Wang%2C%20and%20Nashad%20Singh%20were%20all%20members%20of%20Bankman-Fried's%20inner%20circle%20who%20testified%20against%20him.%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBankman-Fried%20testified%20that%2C%20based%20on%20his%20understanding%20of%20FTX's%20terms%20of%20service%2C%20Alameda's%20role%20as%20a%20payment%20processor%20and%20stablecoin%20convertor%20on%20FTX%2C%20and%20the%20payment%20agreement%20between%20Alameda%20and%20FTX%2C%20there%20could%20arise%20a%20scenario%20where%20the%20funds%20of%20many%20customers%20could%20be%20used%20as%20collateral%20for%20a%20massive%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20his%20lawyers%20argued%20in%20their%20opening%20statement%20for%20the%20trial%2C%20is%20what%20happened%20in%20November%20of%202022%3A%20The%20downturn%20in%20the%20cryptocurrency%20market%20caused%20Alameda%20to%20lose%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20and%20many%20customers%20had%20%26quot%3Bsocialized%20losses%26quot%3B%20as%20collateral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESassoon%2C%20questioning%20Bankman-Fried%20on%20the%20witness%20stand%2C%20asked%20Bankman-Fried%20to%20be%20more%20explicit%20about%20why%20he%20thought%20that%20explanation%20was%20acceptable.%20Alameda%2C%20she%20pointed%20out%2C%20was%20treated%20differently%20from%20every%20other%20customer%20on%20the%20FTX%20exchange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20pulled%20up%20the%20payment%20agreement%20between%20FTX%20and%20Alameda%20%E2%80%94%20which%20Bankman-Fried%20signed%20twice%2C%20once%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20FTX%20and%20once%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20Alameda%20%E2%80%94%20and%20asked%20him%20which%20part%20of%20the%20contract%20said%20it%20was%20OK%20to%20use%20customer%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankman-Fried%20gave%20a%20rambling%20response%20that%20started%20with%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20should%20preface%20this%20by%20saying%20I'm%20not%20a%20lawyer%26quot%3B%20and%20did%20not%20answer%20the%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohen%20repeatedly%20argued%20that%20Sassoon's%20questions%2C%20which%20stretched%20beyond%20the%20trial's%20usual%204%3A30%20p.m.%20ending%20time%2C%20were%20well%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20deposition%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaplan%20allowed%20most%20of%20the%20questions%20to%20move%20through%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20directly%20by%20Sassoon%20if%20it%20was%20OK%20to%20steal%20customer%20funds%2C%20Bankman-Fried%20rejected%20that%20interpretation%20of%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20not%20what%20I%20viewed%20to%20be%20happening%2C%20and%20that%20is%20certainly%20not%20how%20I%20discussed%20it%20with%20attorneys%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaplan%20sustained%20an%20objection%20from%20Cohen%20to%20another%20question%20from%20Sassoon%2C%20directly%20answering%20if%20it%20was%20OK%20to%20embezzle%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankman-Fried%20answered%20anyway%3A%20Of%20course%20it%20wasn't%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20answer%20that%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20to%20laughter%20in%20the%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-ftx-testifies-criminal-fraud-trial-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBankman-Fried's%20risky%20decision%20to%20testify%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20for%20a%20busy%20day%20in%20the%20courthouse.%20In%20line%20for%20security%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20day%2C%20Bankman-Fried's%20stoic%20parents%20grumbled%20to%20each%20other%20about%20press%20photographers%20taking%20their%20picture%20through%20the%20window.%20Asked%20how%20she%20was%20feeling%20about%20the%20day%2C%20his%20mother%20Barbara%20Fried%20offered%20a%20tight-lipped%20shrug.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohen%20distinguished%20Bankman-Fried's%20situation%20from%20Kaplan's%20hypothetical%20bank%20robbery%20case%2C%20noting%20that%20such%20a%20theft%20is%20clearly%20wrong.%20But%20in%20this%20case%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20defense's%20position%20is%20that%20the%20use%20of%20funds%20was%20not%20improper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20client%20is%20doing%20something%20he%20thinks%20is%20proper%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20commercial%20conduct%20is%20inconclusive%20or%20unclear.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Bankman-Fried%20was%20excused%20at%205%20p.m.%2C%20Kaplan%20said%20he%20would%20take%20the%20night%20to%20consider%20whether%20his%20statements%20could%20be%20shared%20with%20the%20jury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBank