20think%20about%20ancient%20civilizations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELong-held%20theories%20about%20the%20collapse%20of%20ancient%20civilizations%20are%20starting%20to%20change.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClimate%20change%20wasn't%20the%20only%20factor%20in%20their%20collapse%2C%20but%20it%20played%20a%20large%20role.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EColiseums%2C%20giant%20stone%20heads%2C%20abandoned%20gardens%2C%20and%20ancient%20signs%20of%20plumbing%20are%20all%20signs%20of%20a%20prosperous%20and%20intelligent%20ancient%20civilization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20leave%20it%20all%20behind%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20scientists%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20solve%20these%20mysteries%20and%20have%20developed%20varying%20theories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20with%20our%20current%20reckoning%20with%20a%20volatile%20climate%2C%20researchers%20are%20starting%20to%20apply%20the%20lens%20of%20climate%20change%20to%20the%20collapse%20of%20ancient%20civilizations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20carbon%20dating%2C%20isotopes%20in%20river%20or%20lake%20sediment%2C%20coring%20trees%2C%20and%20a%20variety%20of%20other%20techniques%2C%20scientists%20are%20starting%20to%20gain%20a%20better%20understanding%20of%20climate%20change%20as%20a%20contributing%20factor%20to%20ancient%20societal%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAncient%20Rome%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20the%20Roman%20Coliseum.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536dcc196908fd7cdb5990d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221660%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Roman%20Coliseum%20is%20an%20enduring%20symbol%20of%20the%20great%20Roman%20Empire.%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwomen-shocked-that-men-regularly-think-about-the-roman-empire-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoman%20Empire%20has%20been%20on%20the%20mind%20lately%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20for%20all%20its%20greatness%2C%20we%20can't%20help%20but%20wonder%20what%20happened%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Roman%20Empire%20is%20lauded%20for%20its%20population%20and%20geographic%20size%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fscience-nature%2Fhow-climate-change-and-disease-helped-fall-rome-180967591%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520effort%2520to%2520put%2520climate%2Cand%2520fall%2520of%2520Roman%2520civilization%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E75%20million%20citizens%20at%20its%20peak%20and%20extending%20from%20northern%20Britain%20to%20the%20edges%20of%20the%20Sahara%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20more%20impressive%20a%20civilization%2C%20the%20more%20of%20a%20spectacle%20it%20becomes%20when%20it%20collapses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Roman%20Empire%20had%20everything%20going%20for%20it%20%E2%80%94%20interconnected%20cities%2C%20a%20universal%20currency%2C%20highways%2C%20libraries%2C%20and%20even%20a%20functioning%20sewage%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20collection%20of%20things%20contributed%20to%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Roman%20Empire.%20However%2C%20researchers%20are%20now%20suggesting%20that%20climate%20change%20contributed%20to%20the%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Roman%20Empire%20benefitted%20from%20warm%2C%20wet%2C%20and%20stable%20weather%20that%20allowed%20abundant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2011%2F01%2F22%2F133143758%2Fcould-climate-change-have-led-to-the-fall-of-rome%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrops%20and%20economic%20success%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20volcanic%20activity%20grew%20and%20led%20the%20world%20into%20the%20%26quot%3BLate%20Antique%20Little%20Ice%20Age%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Roman%20Empire%20began%20to%20lose%20its%20foothold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ice%20age%20led%20to%20low%20crop%20yields%2C%20famine%2C%20and%20poor%20health.%20It%20also%20made%20areas%20of%20the%20Roman%20Empire%20less%20hospitable%20and%20more%20open%20to%20invasion.%20Famine%20and%20poor%20health%20in%20the%20interconnected%2C%20colder%20areas%20of%20the%20Roman%20Empire%20also%20made%20it%20ripe%20for%20a%20plague%20to%20spread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanging%20weather%20introduced%20new%20diseases%2C%20and%20Rome%20dealt%20with%20three%20different%20plagues%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fthe-big-idea%2F2017%2F10%2F30%2F16568716%2Fsix-ways-climate-change-disease-toppled-roman-empire%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmallpox%2C%20the%20Plague%20of%20Cyprian%2C%20and%20the%20bubonic%20plague%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlagues%2C%20famine%2C%20and%20invasion%20all%20befell%20Rome%20as%20the%20weather%20shifted%2C%20contributing%20to%20its%20downfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ENorse%20Civilization%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20glacier%20in%20Greenland.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536aa8f96f7540cd06323be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHahn%20Glacier%20in%20the%20Johan%20Petersen%20Fjord.%3Cp%3EREDA%26amp%3BCO%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Vikings%20first%20settled%20in%20Greenland%20after%20Erik%20Thorvaldsson%2C%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.biography.com%2Fhistory-culture%2Ferik-the-red%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EErik%20the%20Red%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20exiled%20from%20Iceland%20for%20manslaughter%20in%20around%20AD%20985.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20a%20group%20of%20Vikings%20lived%20in%20Greenland%20for%20about%20465%20years%2C%20from%20985%20to%201450.%20But%20suddenly%2C%20they%20disappeared%2C%20leaving%20behind%20their%20homes%20and%20communities%2C%20and%20in%20the%2015th%20century%2C%20signs%20of%20Norse%20habitation%20disappeared%20from%20the%20geological%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20newest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fagu-floods-drove-vikings-from-greenland%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleading%20theory%20is%20that%20climate%20change%20was%20a%20major%20contributing%20factor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20study%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feps.harvard.edu%2Fpeople%2Fmarisa-borreggine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarisa%20Borreggine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20doctoral%20candidate%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Earth%20and%20Planetary%20Sciences%20at%20Harvard%20University%2C%20found%20that%20from%201100%20to%201400%2C%20rising%20sea%20levels%20could%20have%20flooded%20Viking%20settlements%20by%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.2209615120%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E11%20feet%2C%20affecting%2078%20square%20miles%2C%20a%20space%201.5%20times%20the%20size%20of%20San%20Francisco%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20for%20the%20rise%20in%20sea%20levels%20was%20not%20a%20heating%20period%20that%20melted%20glaciers%20and%20caused%20the%20sea%20level%20to%20rise%2C%20but%20the%20Little%20Ice%20Age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Little%20Ice%20Age%20caused%20the%20Southern%20Greenland%20Ice%20Sheet%2C%20the%20nearest%20to%20Norse%20settlements%2C%20to%20grow%20and%20weigh%20down%20the%20land.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20land%20was%20filled%20with%20water.%20The%20ice%20sheet%20even%20grew%20so%20large%20that%20its%20gravity%20pulled%20the%20ocean%20near%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20rising%20sea%20levels%20might%20not%20have%20been%20the%20sole%20reason%20for%20leaving%20Greenland%2C%20it%20was%20certainly%20a%20major%20factor%20when%20compounded%20with%20social%20unrest%2C%20scarcity%20of%20resources%2C%20and%20other%20political%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAngkor%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20the%20ancient%20capital%20Angkor%20Wat%20at%20sunset.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6537c66c0487ff031cac6b60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221609%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAngkor%20Wat%2C%20Cambodia%2C%20at%20sunset%20seen%20in%20a%20reflecting%20pond.%3Cp%3EWolfgang%20Kaehler%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAngkor%20was%20the%20capital%20of%20the%20Khmer%20Empire%20in%20Cambodia.%20It%20was%20labeled%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F12ft.io%2Fproxy%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalgeographic.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fangkor-wat-civilization-collapsed-floods-drought-climate-change%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehydraulic%20city%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20its%20utilization%20of%20local%20water%20sources%20to%20build%20a%20series%20of%20canals%2C%20reservoirs%2C%20dykes%2C%20and%20basins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20peak%2C%20an%20estimated%20750%2C000%20people%20lived%20there%20and%20covered%20400%20square%20miles.%20Research%20has%20begun%20pointing%20toward%20intense%20climate%20change%20as%20a%20significant%20contribution%20to%20the%20collapse%20of%20Angkor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Angkor%20relied%20so%20heavily%20on%20water%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.0910827107%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20at%20Columbia%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%20looked%20at%20the%20tree%20rings%20of%20evergreens%20in%20Cambodia%20to%20understand%20changes%20in%20precipitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20discovered%20that%20in%20the%20century%20before%20it%20collapsed%2C%20Angkor%20encountered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2010%2F03%2F100329203547.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20severe%20%26quot%3Bmegadroughts%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20lasting%2020%20to%2030%20years%2C%20each%20followed%20by%20intense%20monsoons.%20The%20combination%20of%20extreme%20dryness%20and%20intense%20rainfall%20caused%20catastrophic%20flooding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20talking%20about%20dry%20spells%20the%20likes%20of%20which%20we've%20never%20seen%20in%20modern%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20co-author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20Brendan%20M.%20Buckley%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmagazine.columbia.edu%2Farticle%2Fwhat-happened-angkor%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CIt%2520would%2520stand%2520to%2520reason%2Cinto%2520the%2520Little%2520Ice%2520Age.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColumbia%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%2C%20the%20skies%20open%20up%20and%20the%20rain%20won't%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIndus%20Valley%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20the%20foundation%20of%20carious%20brick%20buildings%20leading%20to%20a%20staircase%20and%20a%20larger%20building%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536cc9a96908fd7cdb577d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221684%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20ruins%20of%20the%20archaeological%20site%20of%20Harappa%2C%20Indus%20Valley%20civilisation%2C%203rd%20millennium%20BC%3Cp%3EDEA%20%2F%20G.%20NIMATALLAH%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Indus%20Valley%20civilization%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20populous%20ancient%20civilizations%2C%20potentially%20fell%20due%20in%20part%20to%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Indus%20civilization%20developed%205%2C600%20years%20ago%20and%2C%20at%20its%20peak%2C%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20held%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fid%2Fwbna47600221%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10%25%20of%20the%20world's%20population%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20culture%20that%20expanded%20over%20386%2C000%20square%20miles%2C%20more%20extensive%20than%20ancient%20Egypt%20and%20Mesopotamia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20century%20ago%2C%20archeologists%20began%20finding%20evidence%20of%20old%20cities.%20Evidence%20suggests%20the%20cities%20were%20developed%20with%20grids%20and%20evidence%20of%20advanced%20plumbing%2C%20not%20seen%20again%20until%20Ancient%20Rome.%20Most%20notably%2C%20there%20was%20a%20startling%20lack%20of%20large%20buildings%20for%20royalty%2C%20which%20was%20typical%20of%20civilizations%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20civilization%20so%20populous%2C%20the%20mystery%20of%20why%20so%20many%20cities%20and%20buildings%20were%20abandoned%20seemingly%20overnight%20has%20gone%20unsolved%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20reconstructing%20the%20landscapes%20of%20plains%20and%20rivers%20where%20these%20ancient%20civilizations%20once%20settled%20by%20analyzing%20satellite%20images%20of%20the%20area%20and%20collecting%20sediment%20samples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20these%20methods%2C%20the%20research%20teams%20could%20determine%20what%20crops%20were%20planted%20and%20when%2C%20how%20landscapes%20changed%2C%20and%20how%20that%20affected%20settlements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20cities%20were%20built%20on%20rivers%20fed%20by%20monsoon%20rains.%20As%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2F200-year-drought-doomed-indus-valley-civilization%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20changed%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20the%20monsoons%20became%20less%20frequent%2C%20crops%20and%20water%20sources%20were%20less%20reliable%2C%20facilitating%20a%20move%20east%20towards%20a%20reliable%20water%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20devastated%20the%20Indus%20Civilizations%2C%20which%20relied%20on%20significant%20surplus%20years.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20larger%20cities%20collapsed%20as%20more%20minor%2C%20localized%20communities%20and%20economies%20started%20performing%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETikal%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20the%20ruins%20of%20the%20ancient%20Maya%20Civilization%20in%20Tikal%2C%20Guatemala.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536d06b0487ff031cac135a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221664%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20site%20of%20the%20pre-Colombian%20Maya%20civilization%20in%20Tikal%20National%20Park%2C%20Guatemala.%3Cp%3EVW%20Pics%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETikal%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20founded%20in%20600%20BC%2C%20with%20some%20of%20its%20first%20buildings%20dating%20from%20AD%20250%20to%20900.%20At%20its%20peak%2C%20Tikal%20had%20over%2060%2C000%20citizens%2C%20was%20the%20economic%20hub%20of%20Mayan%20civilization%2C%20and%20occupied%20a%20land%20mass%20about%20the%20size%20of%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20research%20points%20to%20the%20catastrophic%20effect%20of%20drought%20on%20the%20Mayans.%20Researchers%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2F18624-collapse-mayan-civilization-climate-change.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20detailed%20records%20of%20past%20climate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20obtained%20from%20three%20nearby%20lakes%20and%20a%20stalagmite%20on%20a%20cave%20floor%2C%20developing%20a%20model%20of%20the%20balance%20between%20evaporation%20and%20rainfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20point%20to%20intense%20droughts%20lasting%20for%20a%20decade%2C%20mainly%20from%20decreased%20summer%20rain%20activity.%20The%20Mayans%20had%20bet%20on%20summer%20rains%20to%20aid%20their%20farming%20practices%2C%20so%20the%20effects%20were%20catastrophic%20when%20rainfall%20was%20reduced%20by%20even%20a%20modest%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELayered%20on%20top%20of%20the%20drought%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D153b09536b6d62b8dba8b95edd1f70d05da07380936ac7377f3cfabd4b7d2c7d%26postID%3D6532bbd0e20e2d7dddabe6f3%26postSlug%3Dphotos-ancient-civilizations-impacted-climate-change-photos-2023-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-020-67044-z%2523ref-CR5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202020%20suggests%20that%20Mayan%20water%20sources%20were%20contaminated%20with%20toxic%20algae%20and%20mercury.%20The%20Mayans%20built%20their%20city%20in%20a%20way%20that%20aimed%20to%20capture%20as%20much%20rainwater%20as%20possible%20in%20centralized%20reservoirs%20in%20the%20city.%20However%2C%20their%20frequent%20use%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2Fworld-news%2F2020-07-03%2Fty-article%2F.premium%2Fdeath-knell-for-mayan-city-inadvertently-poisoned-its-own-water-supply%2F0000017f-e2e5-d568-ad7f-f3efce780000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecinnabar%2C%20a%20mercury-based%20ore%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20mixed%20with%20the%20accumulated%20rainwater%20and%20found%20its%20way%20into%20the%20reservoirs%2C%20turning%20them%20poisonous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20toxic%20algae%2C%20which%20was%20resistant%20to%20high%20temperatures%20from%20boiling%2C%20resulted%20from%20smoky%20fires%20and%20washing%20ceramic%20plates%20in%20the%20reservoirs%2C%20imbuing%20the%20water%20with%20the%20organic%20material%20needed%20for%20the%20algae%20to%20bloom.%20According%20to%20co-author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20Kenneth%20Tankersley%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20water%20would%20have%20looked%20nasty.%20It%20would%20have%20tasted%20nasty.%20Nobody%20would%20have%20wanted%20to%20drink%20that%20water.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompounded%20with%20persistent%20drought%2C%20lack%20of%20drinking%20water%2C%20diminishing%20crops%2C%20and%20proliferating%20disease%2C%20the%20Mayans%20met%20the%20perfect%20storm%20for%20the%20collapse%20of%20a%20civilization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEaster%20Island%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20the%20seascape%20of%20Easter%20Island%2C%20Chile%2C%20with%20a%20view%20of%20the%20Easter%20Island%20statues%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6537d15f356802a56be1fe14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221673%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEaster%20Island%2C%20Chile.%3Cp%3EWolfgang%20Kaehler%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20remote%20island%20of%20Easter%20Island%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Rapa%20Nui%2C%20is%202%2C000%20miles%20west%20of%20South%20America%20and%20has%20long%20been%20a%20cautionary%20tale%20of%20resource%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20years%2C%20the%20leading%20hypothesis%20for%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Rapa%20Nui%20civilization%20was%20attributed%20to%20the%20deforestation%20by%20the%20people%2C%20which%20led%20to%20cannibalization%2C%20warfare%2C%20and%20societal%20decline%2C%20as%20Jared%20Diamond%20detailed%20in%20his%202011%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguinrandomhouse.com%2Fbooks%2F288954%2Fcollapse-by-jared-diamond%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECollapse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20with%20technological%20advances%20and%20methodology%20changes%20in%20the%20last%2020%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Frethinking-easter-islands-historic-collapse%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifferent%20hypotheses%20have%20come%20to%20light%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%20of%20the%20Rapa%20Nui%20causing%20deforestation%2C%20studies%20believe%20rats%20brought%20over%20by%20European%20settlers%20might%20have%20caused%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeforestation%20by%20rats%20and%20the%20introduction%20of%20diseases%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanscientist.org%2Farticle%2Frethinking-the-fall-of-easter-island%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuropean%20settlers%20in%201722%3C%2Fa%3E%20created%20a%20combination%20of%20events%20that%20contributed%20to%20the%20demise%20of%20the%20Rapa%20Nui.%20The%20population%20of%20Rapanui%20dropped%20to%20111%20in%201877%2C%20not%20because%20of%20cannibalism%20but%20because%20of%20slave%20traders%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sapiens.org%2Farchaeology%2Feaster-island-demise%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESapiens%20Anthropology%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20traditional%20narrative%20of%20%26quot%3Becocide%26quot%3B%20done%20by%20the%20Rapa%20Nui%20has%20continually%20been%20contested%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20as%20newer%20research%20has%20pointed%20to%20these%20other%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECahokia%20Civilization%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20mound%20of%20green%20land%20with%20the%20city%20of%20St.%20Louis%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6537dafc96f7540cd063dc54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20mound%20in%20St.%20Louis%20is%20known%20as%20Monks%20Mound%2C%20the%20largest%20prehistoric%20earthen%20construction%20in%20the%20Americas.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Acker%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECahokia%20was%20a%20city%20in%20what%20is%20now%20Illinois%2C%20with%20about%2020%2C000%20people.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-srv%2Fnational%2Fdaily%2Fmarch%2F12%2Fcahokia.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20largest%20cities%20and%20the%20cultural%20and%20political%20center%20of%20Mississippi%20River%20cities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECahokia%20was%20established%20around%20AD%20700%20and%20thrived%20for%20three%20centuries%20before%20its%20collapse.%20The%20collapse%20of%20Cahokia%20is%20attributed%20to%20changing%20weather%20periods.%20Cahokia%20began%20during%20the%20warmer%20%26quot%3BMedieval%20Climatic%20Anomaly%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20its%20collapse%20was%20during%20the%20Little%20Ice%20Age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrevious%20theories%20surrounding%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Cahokia%20suggest%20that%20the%20indigenous%20members%20overharvested%20wood%2C%20causing%20erosion%20and%20flooding.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fthesalt%2F2017%2F02%2F10%2F513963490%2F1-000-years-ago-corn-made-this-society-big-then-a-changing-climate-destroyed-the%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPossible%2520explanations%2520have%2520included%2520massive%2Cthen%2520drove%2520them%2520to%2520collapse.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20conducted%20on%20minerals%20found%20in%20lake%20sediments%3C%2Fa%3E%20offers%20insight%20into%20the%20changing%20temperatures%20and%20water%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20patterns%20are%20similar%20to%20other%20ancient%20civilizations%20that%20grow%20communities%20on%20river%20beds%20%E2%80%94%20intense%20periods%20of%20drought%2C%20followed%20by%20rain%2C%20causing%20flooding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETiwanaku%20Empire%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20stone%20squares%20in%20a%20field%20left%20by%20Pre-inca%20inhabitants.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6537e2c40487ff031cacabf9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221673%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETiwanaku%2C%20a%20pre-Inca%20Site%20in%20Bolivia%20near%20La%20Paz%20and%20Lake%20Titicaca.%3Cp%3EWolfgang%20Kaehler%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Inca%20Empire%20took%20control%20and%20spread%20along%20South%20America%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fscience-nature%2Fbefore-inca-ruled-south-america-tiwanaku-left-mark-andes-180971844%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETiwanaku%20civilization%3C%2Fa%3E%20lived%20and%20prospered%20in%20what%20is%20now%20Lake%20Titicaca%2C%20Bolivia%2C%20from%20AD%20550%20to%20950.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Tiwanaku%20were%20estimated%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwhc.unesco.org%2Fen%2Flist%2F567%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520political%2520dominance%2520of%2520Tiwanaku%2CAndean%2520region%2520of%2520South%2520America.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E50%2C000%20agricultural%20fields%20and%20irrigation%20technology%2C%20allowing%3C%2Fa%3E%20them%20to%20maintain%20production%20despite%20the%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20t