te%20Chief%20Minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%20stating%20in%20a%20written%20reply%20that%20nearly%2078%2C000%20children%20in%20the%20state%20were%20found%20to%20be%20malnourished%20in%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20this%20year%2C%20women%20and%20child%20development%20accounted%20for%20the%20lowest%20number%20of%20questions%20asked%20in%20the%20Assembly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%2029%2C484%20questions%20asked%20in%20the%20Assembly%2C%20the%20highest%20number%20(2%2C205)%20were%20on%20urban%20development%20and%20housing%2C%20followed%20by%20panchayat%20and%20rural%20development%20(2%2C056)%20and%20revenue%20(1%2C997).%20The%20number%20of%20questions%20asked%20on%20women%20and%20child%20development%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20was%20just%20735.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAttendance%20Highs%20%26amp%3B%20Lows%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20on%20the%20performance%20of%20MLAs%20in%20the%20current%20MP%20Vidhan%20Sabha%2C%20legislators%20from%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20cornered%20all%20the%20top%20five%20slots%20in%20terms%20of%20attending%20the%20most%20number%20of%20sittings%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2079%20sittings%20held%2C%20Kunwarji%20Kothar%2C%20ex-minister%20Harishankar%20Khatik%2C%20Dilip%20Singh%20Parihar%2C%20Shyam%20Lal%20Dwivedi%20and%20Sudesh%20Rai%20attended%2097%25%2C%20or%2077%20sittings.%20Of%20these%20five%20MLAs%2C%20however%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20denied%20tickets%20to%20two%20-%20Shyamlal%20Dwivedi%20(Teothar-Rewa)%20and%20Kunwarji%20Kothar%20(Sarangpur-SC).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EClose%20to%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%20were%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20speaker%20Girish%20Gautam%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20who%20had%20an%20attendance%20of%2034%25%2C%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20Minister%20Narottam%20Mishra%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20with%2020%25%2C%20and%20leader%20of%20opposition%20Dr%20Govind%20Singh%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20whose%20attendance%20figure%20was%2037%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20parties%2C%20the%20BSP%20with%20just%20two%20MLAs%20(one%20of%20whom%20switched%20over%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%20July%202022)%20and%20SP%20with%20just%20one%20MLA%20(who%20also%20joined%20the%20BJP%20the%20same%20month)%20attended%20an%20average%20of%2065%20out%20of%20the%2079%20sittings%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20BJP%2C%20whose%20members%20attended%20an%20average%20of%2046%20sittings.%20The%20Congress%20was%20very%20close%20behind%2C%20with%20its%20MLAs%20attending%20an%20average%20of%2043%20sittings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuestions%20Posed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20did%20well%20in%20terms%20of%20asking%20questions%20as%20well%2C%20with%20four%20of%20its%20MLAs%20featuring%20in%20the%20top%20five%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20maximum%20number%20of%20queries%20posed%20in%20the%20Vidhan%20Sabha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20former%20minister%20Rampal%20Singh%20topped%20with%20390%20questions%2C%20journalist-turned-third-time%20MLA%20from%20Mandsaur%20seat%20Yashpal%20Singh%20Sisodiya%20was%20close%20behind%20with%20387%20questions.%20The%20two%20other%20BJP%20MLAs%20in%20the%20list%20were%20Umakant%20Sharma%20with%20381%20questions%20and%20Rajendra%20Pandey%20with%20377%20questions.%20The%20lone%20Congress%20MLA%20was%20doctor-turned-first-time%20legislator%20Dr%20Hiralal%20Alawa%2C%20a%20tribal%2C%20who%20asked%20383%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20the%20average%20number%20of%20questions%20asked%20by%20various%20parties%2C%20the%20two-MLA-strong%20BSP%20asked%20an%20average%20of%20143%20questions%2C%20Congress%20MLAs%20asked%20an%20average%20of%20132%20questions%20and%20those%20of%20the%20BJP%20asked%20an%20average%20of%2093%20questions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20legislative%20assembly%20sat%20for%20an%20average%20of%20only%2016%20days%20per%20year%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2026%20sittings%20in%202019%20and%20a%20low%20of%20only%20four%20sittings%20in%20Covid-hit%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698334920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fmkt7ecg8_madhya-pradesh-assembly-shivraj_625x300_26_October_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Foutgoing-madhya-pradesh-assembly-sat-for-just-16-days-in-a-year-4517213%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Not%20only%20did%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Assembly%20sit%20for%20an%20average%20of%20only%2016%20days%20a%20year%20-%20compared%20to%2027%20days%20in%20the%20previous%20term%20and%2033%20in%20the%20term%20before%20that%20-%20its%20speaker%2C%20parliamentary%20affairs%20minister%20and%20leader%20of%20opposition%20had%20low%20attendance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Foutgoing-madhya-pradesh-assembly-sat-for-just-16-days-in-a-year-4517213%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Foutgoing-madhya-pradesh-assembly-sat-for-just-16-days-in-a-year-4517213%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Foutgoing-madhya-pradesh-assembly-sat-for-just-16-days-in-a-year-4517213%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SBI%20mulls%20to%20raise%20up%20to%20Rs%2010%2C000%20cr%20tier-II%20bond%20issue%20next%20week%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698334401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-02%2F02%2Ffull%2F1675329282-6264.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsbi-mulls-to-raise-up-to-rs-10-000-cr-tier-ii-bond-issue-next-week-123102601278_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bonds%20are%20rated%20AAA%20by%20consulting%20and%20rating%20firms%20CRISIL%20and%20India%20Ratings%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsbi-mulls-to-raise-up-to-rs-10-000-cr-tier-ii-bond-issue-next-week-123102601278_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsbi-mulls-to-raise-up-to-rs-10-000-cr-tier-ii-bond-issue-next-week-123102601278_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsbi-mulls-to-raise-up-to-rs-10-000-cr-tier-ii-bond-issue-next-week-123102601278_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ethics%20Committee%20on%20Mahua%20Moitra's%20Adani%20Questions%20Sees%20'Vertical%20Spilt'%20between%20BJP%2C%20Opposition%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F03143050%2FDBTy8XrWAAAFLVI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20first%20day%20of%20the%20House%20Ethics%20Committee%20meeting%2C%20called%20to%20look%20into%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%E2%80%99s%20complaint%20against%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%20about%20allegedly%20accepting%20bribes%20to%20ask%20questions%20in%20parliament%2C%20saw%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvertical%20split%E2%80%9D%20between%20the%20Opposition%20and%20the%20ruling%20party%20MPs%20on%C2%A0when%20to%20summon%20Moitra%20to%20depose%20before%20it.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20its%20way%20by%20dint%20of%20sheer%20numbers%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra%20should%20have%20been%20called%20ahead%20of%20the%20complainants%20according%20to%20several%20MPs%20who%20cited%20normal%20procedure%20to%20object%20to%20the%20latter%20being%20given%20time%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20opposition%20MP%2C%20eleven%20of%20the%2015%20MPs%20who%20are%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20formed%20by%20speaker%20Om%20Birla%20earlier%20this%20month%20were%20present%20in%20Thursday%E2%80%99s%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20chairman%20and%20BJP%20MP%20Vinok%20Kumar%20Sonkar%20called%20for%20a%20vote%20in%20which%20the%20BJP%20MPs%20fell%20in%20line.%20There%20was%20a%205-5%20split%20between%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20the%20Opposition%20MPs%20and%20the%20chair%20got%20to%20cast%20the%20deciding%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20stumbling%20block%2C%20once%20the%20opposition%20was%20overruled%2C%20was%20when%20Moitra%20should%20be%20given%20time.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20chairman%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20call%20her%20on%20October%2031%20prevailed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20the%20five%20opposition%20MPs%20present%20in%20the%20meeting%20who%20told%20the%20chairman%20to%20call%20Moitra%20after%20November%2011%20because%20of%20the%20ongoing%20festivities%2C%E2%80%9D%20one%20MP%20present%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Five%20BJP%20MPs%20who%20were%20present%20there%20also%20initially%20said%20so.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20Sonkar%20was%20keen%20on%20summoning%20her%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%A6%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20Moitra%20has%20been%20called%20on%20October%2031%3B%20it%20is%20by%20dint%20of%20the%20numbers%20that%20the%20BJP%20had%20its%20way%20in%20the%20committee.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20committee%20member%20told%20this%20correspondent%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20Opposition%20MPs%20questioned%20the%20chairman%20for%20calling%20the%20complainant%20first%20and%20not%20the%20accused.%20The%20House%20Ethics%20Committee%20is%20also%20ruled%20by%20the%20same%20directorate%20as%20the%20Privilege%20Committee%20which%20summons%20the%20accused%20first%20to%20depose%20before%20it.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20in%20the%20first%20meeting%20itself%2C%20before%20the%20members%20could%20first%20assemble%20to%20understand%20the%20complaint%2C%20the%20chairman%20called%20the%20complainants%2C%20Dubey%20and%20the%20lawyer%20Jai%20Anant%20Dehadrai.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20was%20odd%20was%20also%20that%20the%20chairman%20began%20the%20meeting%20by%20complimenting%20Dehadrai%20as%20a%20very%20senior%20lawyer%2C%20etc.%20Such%20cordiality%20between%20the%20complainants%20and%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee%20was%20striking.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20chairman%20also%20read%20out%20everything%20from%20a%20paper.%20Since%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20meeting%20were%20going%20as%20per%20that%20written%20paper%2C%20it%20seemed%20to%20me%20that%20the%20course%20of%20the%20meeting%20was%20pre-decided.%20When%20an%20Opposition%20MP%20was%20asking%20some%20questions%20to%20the%20chairman%2C%20he%20also%20read%20out%20from%20that%20paper%20to%20say%20to%20him%20that%20such%20questioning%20would%20not%20be%20acceptable%20in%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20meeting.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20cross-questioning%2C%20Dubey%20was%20pointedly%20asked%20about%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20allegation%20that%20he%20had%20cited%20a%20fake%20MBA%20degree%20in%20his%20election%20nomination%20affidavit.%20The%20TMC%20MP%2C%20pointing%20it%20out%20to%20the%20Speaker%2C%20had%20asked%20recently%20if%20that%20is%20the%20case%2C%20should%20he%20not%20be%20disqualified%20from%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDubey%20didn%E2%80%99t%20clarify%20whether%20he%20had%20submitted%20a%20fake%20degree%20in%20his%20election%20nomination%20papers%20but%20only%20said%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20didn%E2%80%99t%20entertain%20the%20allegation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDubey%20had%20claimed%20earlier%20that%20Dehradrai%20has%20documents%20to%20prove%20that%20Moitra%20took%20bribes%20from%20businessman%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20to%20pose%20questions%20in%20parliament.%20While%20Dehadrai%20was%20asked%20by%20most%20MPs%20about%20it%2C%20all%20he%20could%20say%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20all%20mentioned%20in%20the%20affidavit.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20opposition%20MP%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CDehradai%20spoke%20that%20line%20over%20a%20dozen%20times%20in%20the%20meeting.%20No%20documents%20were%20submitted%20as%20claimed%20by%20Dubey.%20It%20left%20us%20a%20bit%20confused%20because%20the%20affidavit%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20those%20details%20but%20Dehradai%20kept%20insisting%20it%20is%20all%20in%20there.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20members%20also%20asked%20Dehadrai%20whether%20it%20was%20a%20personal%20fight%20with%20Moitra%20since%20it%20is%20all%20over%20social%20media%20that%20the%20real%20fight%20between%20the%20two%20was%20around%20a%20pet%20dog%20named%20Henry%20which%20Moitra%20refused%20to%20return%20to%20her%20%E2%80%98jilted%20ex%E2%80%99.%20If%20so%2C%20why%20should%20a%20parliamentary%20committee%20get%20into%20it%3F%20%E2%80%9CHe%20mumbled%20something%20but%20didn%E2%80%99t%20deny%20there%20was%20a%20fight%20over%20the%20dog%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20an%20MP%20present%20in%20the%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20Opposition%20MP%20also%20asked%20Dehadrai%20why%20he%20mentioned%20in%20the%20affidavit%20that%20he%20never%20met%20Dubey%20earlier%2C%20while%20a%20video%20shot%20some%20time%20ago%20and%20circulating%20on%20social%20media%20showed%20him%20interacting%20with%20Dubey%20at%20a%20social%20function.%20According%20to%20two%20MPs%2C%20in%20his%20defence%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5BIt%20was%5D%20Not%20%5Ba%5D%20one-to-one%20meeting%20with%20him.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20Opposition%20members%2C%20Preneet%20Kaur%20of%20Congress%2C%20Hemant%20Godse%20of%20Shiv%20Sena%20and%20B.%20Vallabbhaneni%20of%20YSR%20Congress%20were%20absent%20from%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra%20has%20outrightly%20denied%20Dubey%E2%80%99s%20allegations%2C%20while%20highlighting%20that%20it%20had%20come%20soon%20after%20she%20had%20questioned%20his%20%E2%80%98fake%20MBA%20degree%E2%80%99.%20The%20TMC%20MP%20has%20also%20been%20quite%20vocal%20in%20the%20Parliament%20and%20outside%20about%20Gautam%20Adani%2C%20the%20business%20tycoon%20seen%20close%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20More%20details%20on%20the%20complaint%20can%20be%20read%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-modi-government-and-adani-train-guns-on-opposition-mp-mahua-moitra-heres-what-we-know-and-dont-know%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698334246000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F03143050%2FDBTy8XrWAAAFLVI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fethics-committee-summons-mahua-moitra-on-oct-31-ignoring-mps-requests-to-delay-until-festival%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CThe%20chairman%20also%20read%20out%20everything%20from%20a%20paper.%20Since%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20meeting%20were%20going%20as%20per%20that%20written%20paper%2C%20it%20seemed%20to%20me%20that%20the%20course%20of%20the%20meeting%20was%20pre-decided%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20committee%20source%20told%20The%20Wire.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fethics-committee-summons-mahua-moitra-on-oct-31-ignoring-mps-requests-to-delay-until-festival%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Priyanka%20Gandhi%2C%20Himanta%20Sarma%20Get%20Notice%20Over%20Poll%20Code%20Violation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAssam%20Chief%20Minister%20and%20BJP%20leader%20Himanta%20Biswa%20Sarma%20and%20Congress%20General%20Secretary%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra%20have%20been%20served%20notices%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20over%20alleged%20poll%20code%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20(EC)%20told%20both%20the%20leaders%20to%20reply%20to%20the%20notices%20by%20Monday%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20EC%20warned%20it%20will%20presume%20both%20leaders%20have%20nothing%20to%20say%20if%20they%20do%20not%20respond%20before%20the%20deadline%20ends%